  "texts": [
    "The increase in complexity within a system reflects its ongoing efforts to manage and integrate these external influences but through its own operations.",
    "This process of adaptation and differentiation allows the system to remain viable and responsive to changes in its environment.",
    "In that sense, every autopoietic system manages an undetermined environment through its own closure but informationally open to these irritations from 'outside'.",
    "If we use these concepts and elaboration of the social system theory, we could put scientific authorship, as a systemic category, under evaluation as a structural coupling of the psychic system (person), technology and scientific system.",
    "The main characteristic of scientific authorship is one of dynamism and autopoiesis where one component of this coupling cannot be reduced to other."
  ],
